text: Two submarines of the United States Navy have been named USS Swordfish after the swordfish, a large fish with a long, swordlike beak and a high dorsal fin. * , a commissioned in 1939 and sunk in 1945, was the first United States submarine to sink a Japanese ship during World War II. * , a in commission from 1958 to 1989, is accused by Russia of ramming and sinking the during the Cold War (see Project Jennifer).
